# 5. みんな笑顔で

Nene: ...
Classmates: Hey, wanna go to a karaoke place?
Classmates: Yeah, totally! We should also try inviting that other group!
Nene: (What do I do...? Everyone in this class...)
Nene: (They basically all seem like... Extroverts...)
Nene: (How do I fit in here...? What happens if I never really do...?)
Nene: (I did see some familiar names on the roster, but...)
???: Hey!
An: Morning, Kusanagi! So you're also in Class A! Let's have a great year together!
Nene: M-Morning, Shiraishi...
Akito: Never would've guessed they'd put me in the same class as you guys.
Nene: M-Morning...
An: Hey, Akito! You're in this class too?
Akito: Yeah. Wait, didn't you look at the class roster?
An: The roster? Nope. A friend told me which class I'm in, so I didn't have to look. Plus, coming here was the fastest way to see my new classmates.
Akito: True. You've got nerves of steel when it comes to this kind of stuff...
An: What's that supposed to mean? Just so you know, I still care whether or not my friends are in the same class as me.
An: I'm glad, though! It looks like I've talked to basically everyone here at least once before.
Akito: Basically everyone? How many friends do you have...?
An: Hey, aren't a bunch of your friends here too? I see all the soccer guys gathered over there.
Soccer Club Classmates: Hey, Akito! You should come join us!
Akito: Yeah, in a sec.
Nene: (No...)
Nene: (These two... They're so different from me...)
An: Oh, right! Kusanagi!
Nene: Huh? Y-Yeah?
An: Tenma told me everything! You and your troupe are gonna leave the Wonder Stage to train and become better actors, right?
Nene: Y-Yeah...
An: Then, that means we're training buddies!
Nene: Huh? Training buddies?
An: I'm also training to become a better singer. My dad's been taking us to all sorts of different places as a part of that.
Nene: R-Really...? You guys must be working pretty hard if you're traveling that much.
An: We are! That's why I said we're training buddies, since we're both doing what we can to improve!
Nene: Buddies...
Nene: Right... Then, um... Let's do our best.
An: Yeah!
???: Pardon the intrusioooooon!!!
Nene: Uh oh...!
Akito: Huh...?! What are they doing where all the second-years are...?!
Classmates: Hey, isn't that the Weirdo Wombo Combo?!
Classmates: What are they doing in our class?
Nene: J-Just pretend like you don't know them...
Tsukasa: Heeeey! Neneeee! How are you liking your new class?!
Rui: Are you getting along with your new classmates?
Nene: N-No, what are you...?!
Classmates: Nene... Who's that?
Classmates: Oh, they mean Kusanagi. She's over there. She does shows with them.
Classmates: Really? I never would've guessed. She doesn't seem the type.
Nene: Oh geez...!
???: I knew it! See, it was Tsukasa's voice we heard just now!
???: Looks like we weren't mistaken.
Rui: Oh?
Nene: N-Now who's coming...?!
Nene: W-Wait, that looks like...
Rui: Mizuki. Ah, with Aoyagi in tow. Can I assume that...?
Mizuki: Yup! We're both right next door in Class B!
Toya: Akiyama and I were talking just now and suddenly heard a booming voice from this direction...
Toya: We thought it might be Tsukasa, so we decided to see what was going on.
Rui: Ah, and here you both are.
Mizuki: Still, Toya, I'm so glad they put us in the same class.
Mizuki: The teacher asked me to carry a bunch of stuff, but you immediately came to the rescue after I complained how heavy it was♪
Toya: When faced with a classmate in need, isn't it normal to want to help out?
Tsukasa: Indeed! That was very noble of you, Toya!
Akito: Hey, Toya, try not to be so easily fooled in the future...
Rui: Mizuki does have a talent for that. I recommend keeping your cards a little closer to your chest.
Toya: Akiyama's always been very kind to me... I hadn't realized. I'll be more careful.
Mizuki: What?! Rui, don't pile on!
Nene: Haha...
Akito: *Sigh* Talk about a rough road up ahead...
An: Hey, I think they're gonna get along just fine!
Tsukasa: Agreed! If nothing else, I'm happy to see that everyone is all smiles!
Tsukasa: Everyone, let's make this year another good one!
Mizuki: Yeah!
Toya: Yes, let's.
